page.title: 01Land Cover
page.content: This area is part of a densely populated section of West London called North Hammersmith and College Park.The primary land cover is residential. Industry is the secondary land cover. The industry is split into areas of industrial estates, mainly situated in the North-West of the area. A smaller section of the industry is also in the South-East. The railway lines cut the area into three sections with a large siding and depot in the North. This is surrounded by industry and wasteland.The wasteland features in the centre of the area and is quite famous. The canal runs alongside the railway line. There are a few shops gathered togther in areas amongst the houses. There are also various assorted public buildings and two cemeteries.
